- Cops aren't allowed inside the temple.
- You've never been inside?

230
00:23:35,481 --> 00:23:38,897
We keep strict separation so that
no one can be accused of tampering.

231
00:23:39,068 --> 00:23:43,315
- I'll be the first one to go in then?
- Maybe you didn't hear me.

232
00:23:43,531 --> 00:23:47,363
- If it's a question of authority...
- There is no question.

233
00:23:47,535 --> 00:23:49,361
You don't have any.

234
00:23:49,745 --> 00:23:52,865
I have a warrant in my pocket
that says different.

235
00:24:04,426 --> 00:24:07,462
- Show it to me.
- Sure.

236
00:24:12,642 --> 00:24:15,477
This investigation of Precrime
and its personnel is conducted...

237
00:24:15,645 --> 00:24:20,271
...under the direct supervision and
permission from the attorney general.

238
00:24:20,650 --> 00:24:22,726
I'm here as his representative...

239
00:24:22,902 --> 00:24:26,982
...which means you're now operating
under my supervision.

240
00:24:31,368 --> 00:24:34,702
Seems you've been left
out of the loop.

241
00:24:44,256 --> 00:24:47,340
All right, we're ready. Let's go.

242
00:24:53,264 --> 00:24:57,344
<i>- Hold it right there. Hold on.
- Not cleared for access.</i>

243
00:24:58,770 --> 00:25:01,225
<i>Eye-dent: John Anderton. Approved.</i>

244
00:25:08,571 --> 00:25:10,480
- Wally.
- No, no, no, no.

245
00:25:10,656 --> 00:25:13,989
Danny Witwer from Justice.
We're to give him the run of the farm.

246
00:25:14,159 --> 00:25:16,781
- I can't touch you.
- Don't touch anything.

247
00:25:16,954 --> 00:25:20,239
- You can't be in here.
- Just answer his questions.

248
00:25:20,415 --> 00:25:22,989
- Tell me how...
- They're sleeping.

249
00:25:23,168 --> 00:25:26,122
Sorry. Tell me how all this works.

250
00:25:27,297 --> 00:25:30,168
The photon milk acts as both a
nutrient supply and conductor.

251
00:25:30,342 --> 00:25:34,635
It enhances the images they receive.
We call the female Agatha.

252
00:25:34,804 --> 00:25:39,799
The twins are Arthur and Dashiell.
We scan by way of optical tomography.

253
00:25:39,976 --> 00:25:42,846
White-light pinpoints pulse
along the length of the headgear...

254
00:25:43,021 --> 00:25:46,140
...and are reread after absorption
through their brain tissue.

255
00:25:46,941 --> 00:25:49,811
In other words, we see what they see.

256
00:25:51,237 --> 00:25:54,771
They don't feel pain. We keep
their heads stocked with dopamine.

257
00:25:54,949 --> 00:25:58,448
Plus, we maintain careful control
over their serotonin levels.

258
00:25:58,827 --> 00:26:01,614
Don't want them to drift off
into too deep a sleep.

259
00:26:01,789 --> 00:26:06,450
- They can't be kept too awake either.
- Don't think of them as human.

260
00:26:07,252 --> 00:26:10,288
No. They're much more than that.

261
00:26:12,632 --> 00:26:15,669
Science has stolen
most of our miracles.

262
00:26:17,429 --> 00:26:21,509
In a way, they give us hope,
hope of the existence of the divine.

263
00:26:21,683 --> 00:26:25,514
It's interesting that some people
have begun to deify the Pre-Cogs.

264
00:26:25,686 --> 00:26:27,928
Pre-Cogs are pattern-recognition filters.
That's all.

265
00:26:28,105 --> 00:26:31,190
- Yet you call this room the "temple. "
- A nickname.

266
00:26:31,359 --> 00:26:33,517
The oracle isn't where
the power is, anyway.

267
00:26:33,694 --> 00:26:38,356
The power is with the priests,
even if they had to invent the oracle.

268
00:26:39,867 --> 00:26:42,868
You guys are nodding like you know
what he's talking about.

269
00:26:43,287 --> 00:26:47,498
Well, come on, chief. The way we work,
changing destiny and all...

270
00:26:47,666 --> 00:26:49,742
...we're more like clergy than cops.

271
00:26:49,918 --> 00:26:51,543
- Jad.
- Yeah?

272
00:26:51,920 --> 00:26:55,289
Go to work. All of you.

273
00:27:03,389 --> 00:27:05,548
Sorry. Old habit.

274
00:27:05,725 --> 00:27:09,390
I spent three years at Fuller Seminary
before I became a cop.

275
00:27:09,562 --> 00:27:12,812
- My father was proud.
- What does he think of your work?

276
00:27:12,982 --> 00:27:17,691
I don't know. He was shot and killed
when I was 15 at our church in Dublin.

277
00:27:17,862 --> 00:27:20,779
I know what it's like
to lose someone close.

278
00:27:20,948 --> 00:27:23,190
Nothing's like the loss of a child.

279
00:27:23,367 --> 00:27:27,614
I don't have any children, so I can
only imagine what that was like.

280
00:27:27,788 --> 00:27:31,453
To lose your son
in such a public place like that...

281
00:27:31,625 --> 00:27:34,828
Now we can make sure that
kind of thing doesn't happen to anyone.

282
00:27:35,003 --> 00:27:38,751
- Tell me what it is you're looking for.
- Flaws.

283
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:41,795
There hasn't been a murder
in six years. This system is...

284
00:27:41,968 --> 00:27:46,594
Perfect. I agree.
If there's a flaw, it's human.

285
00:27:47,056 --> 00:27:49,096
It always is.

286
00:27:49,934 --> 00:27:51,891
John.

287
00:28:34,477 --> 00:28:35,592
Wally.

288
00:28:41,484 --> 00:28:45,481
Can you see?

289
00:29:17,518 --> 00:29:21,136
What happened? Her ACTH levels
just shot through the roof!

290
00:29:21,314 --> 00:29:23,271
- What'd you do?
- She grabbed me.

291
00:29:23,441 --> 00:29:27,272
Impossible. They're not aware of us.
In the milk, all they see is the future.

292
00:29:27,444 --> 00:29:31,489
- She looked straight at me.
- It could have been a nightmare.

293
00:29:31,657 --> 00:29:34,907
- She spoke to me.
- To you?

294
00:29:35,077 --> 00:29:36,904
What'd she say?

295
00:29:37,079 --> 00:29:39,570
"Can you see?"

296
00:29:59,392 --> 00:30:00,969
You the sentry?

297
00:30:01,727 --> 00:30:04,479
Yes, sir, I'm Gideon.

298
00:30:04,647 --> 00:30:06,723
You're Chief Anderton.

299
00:30:07,483 --> 00:30:10,152
The music relaxes the prisoners.

300
00:30:10,319 --> 00:30:13,818
I don't ever see you Precops down here.
Am I in trouble?

301
00:30:14,114 --> 00:30:17,199
Not yet.
I'm interested in a murder.

302
00:30:17,367 --> 00:30:20,950
- I got plenty of those. Kill type?
- Drowning.

303
00:30:21,121 --> 00:30:24,038
That narrows it down.
Not too many in here for that.

304
00:30:24,207 --> 00:30:27,659
- Victim's Caucasian, female.
- This about the Justice Department?

305
00:30:27,836 --> 00:30:32,296
I'm supposed to spruce up for a tour
they got tomorrow. You like this tie?

306
00:30:32,465 --> 00:30:33,496
Stop.

307
00:30:37,220 --> 00:30:38,595
Roll back.

308
00:30:40,098 --> 00:30:41,378
There.

309
00:30:41,557 --> 00:30:47,393
She's a golden oldie. One of our first.
Probably before your time.

310
00:30:47,772 --> 00:30:51,852
- This is the composite of the three?
- That's right.

311
00:30:52,026 --> 00:30:55,062
Combined data stream
based on all three previsions.

312
00:30:55,237 --> 00:30:58,606
- Just show me Agatha's data stream.
- For that...

313
00:31:00,659 --> 00:31:02,450
...we go for a ride.

314
00:31:24,182 --> 00:31:26,055
My God.

315
00:31:26,350 --> 00:31:28,509
I'd forgotten there were so many.

316
00:31:28,686 --> 00:31:33,597
And to think they'd all be out there
killing people if it wasn't for you.

317
00:31:34,066 --> 00:31:36,983
Look at them.
Look at how peaceful they seem.

318
00:31:37,152 --> 00:31:41,067
But on the inside: Busy, busy, busy.

319
00:31:41,240 --> 00:31:45,783
Okey-pokey.
Now that is one bad man.

320
00:31:45,994 --> 00:31:49,493
He drowned a woman named
Anne Lively out at Roland Lake.

321
00:31:49,664 --> 00:31:53,496
The killer's a John Doe,
never identified.

322
00:32:08,891 --> 00:32:13,103
Why is he still a John Doe?
Why wasn't he ID'd from the eye scan?

323
00:32:13,270 --> 00:32:18,016
Those are not his eyes. He had them
swapped out to fool the scanners.

324
00:32:18,192 --> 00:32:22,189
You can get it done on the street
for a few thousand bucks these days.

325
00:32:22,363 --> 00:32:26,194
Okay, so you want
just the female prevision.

326
00:32:26,366 --> 00:32:27,991
That's right.

327
00:32:34,082 --> 00:32:37,368
We don't seem to have her data.

328
00:32:38,128 --> 00:32:39,836
Try again.

329
00:32:41,256 --> 00:32:44,874
This is odd. See?

330
00:32:45,051 --> 00:32:49,926
We have the two previsions. We got
what Art saw. We got what Dash saw.

331
00:32:50,097 --> 00:32:53,134
But Agatha's isn't here.

332
00:32:55,478 --> 00:32:57,020
Probably just a glitch.

333
00:32:57,188 --> 00:33:01,517
Tell me about the intended victim,
this Anne Lively.

334
00:33:01,900 --> 00:33:05,898
Looks like she's a neuroin addict,
like our John Doe here.

335
00:33:06,071 --> 00:33:09,025
Address history
includes the Beaton Clinic.

336
00:33:09,199 --> 00:33:12,402
So she cleaned up.
Where is she now?

337
00:33:14,079 --> 00:33:16,914
I guess glitches come in twos.

338
00:33:18,291 --> 00:33:23,333
You finally crawl your way out
of one hole just to fall into another.

339
00:33:28,509 --> 00:33:29,541
No.

340
00:33:30,928 --> 00:33:33,965
Can't let you take that out of here,
chief.

341
00:33:34,765 --> 00:33:38,549
- It's against the rules.
- Anything else against the rules?

342
00:33:44,024 --> 00:33:50,276
Careful, chief. You dig up the past,
all you get is dirty.

343
00:33:54,951 --> 00:33:58,534
The third prevision was what,
kind of fuzzy or something?

344
00:33:58,747 --> 00:34:02,958
No, the third prevision,
Agatha's prevision, wasn't there.

345
00:34:03,168 --> 00:34:08,292
That's not all. There are a dozen more
cases with missing previsions.

346
00:34:08,464 --> 00:34:11,714
You'd think we'd have found
the cure for the common cold.

347
00:34:11,926 --> 00:34:14,215
- It's stress.
- What's this?

348
00:34:14,429 --> 00:34:16,386
Herbal tea with honey.

349
00:34:16,597 --> 00:34:20,096
I hate herbal tea.
Almost as much as I hate honey.

350
00:34:20,309 --> 00:34:23,144
Just drink it,
before I pour it in your lap.

351
00:34:23,312 --> 00:34:26,183
- Can I get you anything, John?
- No, thank you.

352
00:34:26,565 --> 00:34:30,148
Witwer's scheduled for a tour
of Containment tomorrow.

353
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:32,318
Yeah, give him a tour.

354
00:34:33,697 --> 00:34:36,188
- Lara called me.
- What?

355
00:34:36,825 --> 00:34:40,158
She's worried about you.
Quite frankly, so am I.

356
00:34:40,912 --> 00:34:42,241
I'm fine.

357
00:34:42,455 --> 00:34:46,323
I understand you've been spending
a lot of time in the Sprawl.

358
00:34:47,669 --> 00:34:50,670
- I go running down there.
- In the middle of the night.

359
00:34:51,339 --> 00:34:54,423
What if Danny Witwer
insisted on a full chem run?

360
00:34:54,634 --> 00:34:56,294
I'm fine.

361
00:34:57,804 --> 00:35:02,264
The minute Precrime goes national,
they are going to take it away.

362
00:35:02,475 --> 00:35:04,800
- We won't let them.
- No?

363
00:35:05,019 --> 00:35:09,312
How is an old man and a cop on the
whiff ever going to stop them?

364
00:35:10,024 --> 00:35:12,312
My father once said to me...

365
00:35:12,526 --> 00:35:16,689
..."You don't choose the things
you believe in. They choose you. "

366
00:35:16,863 --> 00:35:18,773
There's a reason you are here.

367
00:35:18,991 --> 00:35:24,744
Had Precrime been in place earlier,
your loss would have been prevented.

368
00:35:24,955 --> 00:35:26,497
Remember, the eyes...

369
00:35:28,833 --> 00:35:32,249
The eyes of the nation
are on us right now.

370
00:35:32,587 --> 00:35:35,790
I'm not the generation
anyone listens to...

371
00:35:36,007 --> 00:35:40,170
...but people trust you when you
speak of your belief in Precrime.

372
00:35:40,761 --> 00:35:45,222
They know that it's a belief born of
pain, not politics. I understood that.

373
00:35:45,391 --> 00:35:48,974
I may have even encouraged it
to help with the cause.

374
00:35:50,563 --> 00:35:54,560
But now,
your pain is hurting both of us.

375
00:35:58,570 --> 00:36:01,239
They're not going to take it
away from us.

376
00:36:02,240 --> 00:36:03,900
I won't let them.

377
00:36:34,563 --> 00:36:35,974
Bingo.

378
00:36:49,160 --> 00:36:50,987
<i>- Hi, Daddy.
- Hey, buddy.</i>

379
00:36:51,204 --> 00:36:53,113
<i>- I made up a club.
- Yeah?</i>

380
00:36:53,331 --> 00:36:56,949
<i>- We're called the Crescos.
- The Crescos.</i>

381
00:36:57,168 --> 00:36:59,659
<i>- We made up a soccer team.
- Yeah?</i>

382
00:36:59,879 --> 00:37:02,584
<i>- We practice at school.
- With Connor?</i>

383
00:37:02,799 --> 00:37:05,835
Your daddy's in a lot of trouble,
Sean.

384
00:37:30,867 --> 00:37:33,323
- Wait!
- No!

385
00:37:35,997 --> 00:37:38,702
Jad, how come you're not with
Father Witwer?

386
00:37:38,917 --> 00:37:44,670
We're in motion on something. We got a
white, male victim, about 5' 10", 170.

387
00:37:44,839 --> 00:37:47,412
He takes a round in the 10-ring
and goes out a window.

388
00:37:47,633 --> 00:37:49,425
- Red Ball?
- Nope. Brown Ball.

389
00:37:49,635 --> 00:37:50,833
It's premeditated.

390
00:37:51,053 --> 00:37:54,671
Amazing. There's someone within
200 miles still dumb enough to do that.

391
00:37:54,849 --> 00:37:56,391
The victim's name is Leo Crow.

392
00:37:56,600 --> 00:38:01,143
This is case number 1109. Time of
occurrence: Friday, 1506 hours.

393
00:38:01,355 --> 00:38:05,815
Start search for Leo Crow. Case 1109,
previsualized by the Pre-Cogs...

394
00:38:06,026 --> 00:38:09,311
...recorded on holosphere
by Precrime's Q-stacks.

395
00:38:09,529 --> 00:38:13,990
My fellow witnesses are Dr. Katherine
James and Chief Justice Frank Pollard.

396
00:38:14,201 --> 00:38:15,445
Good morning.

397
00:38:15,660 --> 00:38:18,330
Are you ready
to preview and validate 1109?

398
00:38:18,538 --> 00:38:21,455
<i>- Ready when you are, John.
- Standing by.</i>

399
00:38:27,213 --> 00:38:29,004
I love this part.

400
00:38:30,049 --> 00:38:35,043
I've got no address. No tax returns
for the last five years.

401
00:38:35,221 --> 00:38:37,794
Check NCIC.
Maybe he's got a number.

402
00:38:38,641 --> 00:38:42,389
We'll send a protection team
as soon as we lock location.

403
00:38:45,522 --> 00:38:48,227
It looks like federal housing.
Concrete, glass, egg crates.

404
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:51,484
Ouch. About a thousand of those
in the District.

405
00:38:52,988 --> 00:38:54,779
Fractured images coming in.

406
00:38:54,990 --> 00:38:57,362
Numbers nine...

407
00:38:59,911 --> 00:39:01,619
Nine, six.

408
00:39:06,209 --> 00:39:10,206
Female, senior. She's smoking a pipe.

409
00:39:11,047 --> 00:39:12,327
She's laughing.

410
00:39:15,927 --> 00:39:18,049
Okay, now I'm inside a room.

411
00:39:18,971 --> 00:39:21,723
Windowpanes, aluminum extrusion.

412
00:39:22,266 --> 00:39:25,433
Two figures resolving in the room.

413
00:39:26,478 --> 00:39:28,601
<i>- Wait!
- No...</i>

414
00:39:32,150 --> 00:39:34,357
Looks like we got a third party.

415
00:39:35,237 --> 00:39:37,906
Wearing sunglasses,
just out the window.

416
00:39:38,615 --> 00:39:40,572
You're not gonna kill me.

417
00:39:43,119 --> 00:39:44,779
Goodbye, Crow.

418
00:39:50,710 --> 00:39:52,584
<i>You're not gonna kill me.</i>

419
00:39:52,962 --> 00:39:54,955
<i>- Goodbye, Crow.
- Wait!</i>

420
00:39:58,843 --> 00:40:00,966
Wait. Wait.

421
00:40:01,470 --> 00:40:03,379
You say something, chief?

422
00:40:03,597 --> 00:40:04,795
No.

423
00:40:08,310 --> 00:40:09,970
I'll get this one.

424
00:40:10,437 --> 00:40:12,477
We got time on this one, Jad.

425
00:40:12,648 --> 00:40:15,602
Mind getting me a piece
of cake they're eating?

426
00:40:15,817 --> 00:40:17,644
- I'm starving.
- Sure, chief.

427
00:40:17,819 --> 00:40:20,654
I think I'll get one for myself too.

428
00:40:20,822 --> 00:40:22,316
Take your time.

429
00:40:39,006 --> 00:40:42,671
<i>Chief Anderton,
what is this that I'm seeing?</i>

430
00:40:43,386 --> 00:40:44,880
<i>I'm confused about...</i>

431
00:41:16,793 --> 00:41:18,832
<i>- Anderton, wait!
- Goodbye, Crow.</i>

432
00:41:19,045 --> 00:41:20,373
<i>Anderton, wait!</i>

433
00:41:22,256 --> 00:41:24,165
<i>Anderton, wait!</i>

434
00:41:30,347 --> 00:41:34,131
I like you, chief.
You've always been nice to me.

435
00:41:36,395 --> 00:41:39,396
Give you two minutes
before I hit the alarm.

436
00:41:55,788 --> 00:41:57,199
Hold that, please.

437
00:41:58,499 --> 00:41:59,744
Thanks.

438
00:42:03,045 --> 00:42:06,710
- You're in a lot of trouble, John.
- You set me up.

439
00:42:06,924 --> 00:42:09,842
I'll write the paranoia off to the
whiff you've been doping on.

440
00:42:10,052 --> 00:42:11,297
Easy.

441
00:42:11,512 --> 00:42:13,754
- Easy.
- Seems I've found a flaw.

442
00:42:16,266 --> 00:42:17,464
What are you gonna do?

443
00:42:17,684 --> 00:42:20,602
Possession will cost you six months
and your badge.

444
00:42:20,771 --> 00:42:23,262
I guess we won't be working together
after all.

445
00:42:23,482 --> 00:42:27,100
Now put the gun down, John.
I don't hear a Red Ball.

446
00:42:48,547 --> 00:42:50,623
<i>Lamar. Lamar.</i>

447
00:42:53,219 --> 00:42:55,591
<i>- Lamar?
- John, what is happening?</i>

448
00:42:55,804 --> 00:42:57,797
It's Witwer. He set me up!

449
00:42:57,973 --> 00:42:59,302
Stop, just wait.

450
00:42:59,475 --> 00:43:02,428
- Witwer! It's Witwer.
- Who's the victim?

451
00:43:02,644 --> 00:43:04,269
<i>- Somebody.
- Who?</i>

452
00:43:04,479 --> 00:43:06,472
<i>- Somebody... Leo Crow.
- Who is he?</i>

453
00:43:06,690 --> 00:43:09,441
I have no idea!
I've never heard of him.

454
00:43:09,651 --> 00:43:12,652
But I'm supposed to kill him
in less than 36 hours.

455
00:43:12,821 --> 00:43:16,106
- How could Witwer have access?
- Can you fake a cerebral output?

456
00:43:16,324 --> 00:43:17,949
<i>- Why would anyone want to?
- Can you?</i>

457
00:43:18,159 --> 00:43:20,484
- I doubt it.
- Would Hineman know?

458
00:43:20,662 --> 00:43:22,738
<i>- Now listen, come in.
- What?</i>

459
00:43:22,956 --> 00:43:25,363
I'll protect you until we
get to the bottom of this.

460
00:43:25,583 --> 00:43:28,619
Talk to Wally. See if Witwer's gone
inside the temple again.

461
00:43:28,836 --> 00:43:32,287
Ask Jad for any off-hour
eye-dents into the analytical room.

462
00:43:33,049 --> 00:43:34,840
Who's Leo Crow?

463
00:43:35,050 --> 00:43:37,838
<i>Security lockdown enabled.
Revised destination: Office.</i>

464
00:43:38,012 --> 00:43:40,716
Lamar, they found me.

465
00:43:45,143 --> 00:43:48,347
Is there any way to override
the lockdown?

466
00:43:48,563 --> 00:43:50,473
<i>- No, no, no.
- No?</i>

467
00:43:50,690 --> 00:43:54,190
<i>I'll meet you anywhere you say.
You can come to my house, John.</i>

468
00:43:54,402 --> 00:43:56,976
I can't. They'll get me.
I'm not gonna get haloed.

469
00:43:57,197 --> 00:43:58,311
You can't run.

470
00:43:59,282 --> 00:44:00,527
Everybody runs.

471
00:44:47,578 --> 00:44:49,488
- Oh, my God!
- Hey, hey.

472
00:45:04,094 --> 00:45:06,764
Oh, my gosh, are you okay?

473
00:45:10,017 --> 00:45:12,223
I'll bring him in. Unharmed.

474
00:45:12,436 --> 00:45:15,105
You're not gonna do that.
I'm taking control.

475
00:45:15,272 --> 00:45:16,517
What?

476
00:45:16,731 --> 00:45:21,144
Fletcher is second in command.
It's his show to run. You can observe.

477
00:45:21,361 --> 00:45:24,730
- Do it. Find him.
- Yes, sir.

478
00:45:26,741 --> 00:45:30,359
He came to see you the other day
right before he was tagged.

479
00:45:30,578 --> 00:45:33,151
- What did you talk about?
- The Mets.

480
00:45:33,372 --> 00:45:36,207
John doesn't think they have a deep
enough pitching roster.

481
00:45:36,417 --> 00:45:40,284
Why are you protecting him? You knew
he was doping, yet you did nothing.

482
00:45:40,504 --> 00:45:43,838
- The man lost a child, for chrissake.
- Six years ago.

483
00:45:44,049 --> 00:45:47,086
- What did you talk about?
- None of your business.

484
00:45:47,303 --> 00:45:51,799
It's my business. Investigation of a
supervising officer for a capital crime...

485
00:45:51,974 --> 00:45:56,102
...falls under federal jurisdiction
so as to rule out any conspiracy.

486
00:45:56,311 --> 00:45:58,719
- He's my suspect.
- He's my subordinate.

487
00:45:58,939 --> 00:46:02,557
Call the attorney general. I'm sure
he'd clarify the issue for you.

488
00:46:02,776 --> 00:46:06,109
I don't want John Anderton hurt.

489
00:46:07,989 --> 00:46:10,361
I'm going to enjoy working here.

490
00:46:13,244 --> 00:46:15,486
<i>A road diverges in the desert.</i>

491
00:46:16,080 --> 00:46:17,409
<i>Lexus.</i>

492
00:46:17,623 --> 00:46:21,491
<i>The road you're on, John Anderton,
is the one less-traveled.</i>

493
00:46:21,711 --> 00:46:24,830
<i>- Make sure you...
- Diamonds...</i>

494
00:46:27,007 --> 00:46:29,130
<i>Good evening, John Anderton.</i>

495
00:46:32,346 --> 00:46:36,260
<i>John Anderton! You could use
a Guinness right about now.</i>

496
00:46:38,769 --> 00:46:41,520
<i>- John Anderton...
- Escape from it all.</i>

497
00:46:41,730 --> 00:46:46,392
<i>Get away, John Anderton.
Forget your troubles.</i>

498
00:47:03,376 --> 00:47:07,836
He's been eye-dented on the Metro.
The train stops at 20th and 33rd.

499
00:47:08,047 --> 00:47:09,838
Send units to each location.

500
00:47:10,049 --> 00:47:11,840
- Better make 20th.
- Have faith.

501
00:47:52,882 --> 00:47:54,292
Fire them up!

502
00:48:18,448 --> 00:48:20,440
- Hey, Fletch.
- Hey, John.

503
00:48:20,616 --> 00:48:22,775
- That was a rough landing.
- Yeah.

504
00:48:22,952 --> 00:48:25,408
- Work on that.
- It's the shit knee of mine.

505
00:48:25,621 --> 00:48:27,530
- Yeah.
- Don't do it.

506
00:48:28,291 --> 00:48:30,117
Hey, don't do this.

507
00:48:30,876 --> 00:48:32,121
John?

508
00:48:32,461 --> 00:48:33,790
Don't run.

509
00:48:34,296 --> 00:48:36,336
You don't have to chase me.

510
00:48:36,924 --> 00:48:38,584
You don't have to run.

511
00:48:38,926 --> 00:48:40,799
Everybody runs, Fletch.

512
00:48:41,011 --> 00:48:43,004
You know we'll catch you.

513
00:48:44,014 --> 00:48:45,722
Everybody runs.

514
00:48:47,684 --> 00:48:51,812
- It doesn't have to be like this, John.
- Everybody runs.

515
00:48:51,980 --> 00:48:54,103
Get your sick-sticks ready.

516
00:48:55,483 --> 00:48:57,227
Everybody runs, Fletch.

517
00:48:57,777 --> 00:49:00,350
Slow down, chief. Just take it easy.

518
00:49:04,367 --> 00:49:06,276
No sudden moves, chief.

519
00:49:07,495 --> 00:49:09,487
John, it's okay.

520
00:49:09,956 --> 00:49:12,162
- Fletch...
- Easy does it, chief.

521
00:49:40,777 --> 00:49:42,022
Got a grip?

522
00:49:42,195 --> 00:49:43,938
- Got a grip?
- Yeah.

523
00:50:12,724 --> 00:50:14,135
Anderton!

524
00:50:45,297 --> 00:50:48,002
Go away! Get out of my kitchen!

525
00:50:48,217 --> 00:50:51,253
Get out of my house!
Get out of my house! Go!

526
00:50:54,264 --> 00:50:56,755
- Get them out of here!
- Anderton, stop!

527
00:50:56,933 --> 00:50:59,638
Pull him off me, Fletcher.
Get him off me.

528
00:51:01,354 --> 00:51:04,557
Get him out of here!
What's the matter with you?!

529
00:51:09,654 --> 00:51:11,860
Get out of my house! Go!

530
00:51:32,426 --> 00:51:36,719
By mandate of the District of Columbia,
I'm placing you under arrest for...

531
00:51:36,930 --> 00:51:38,258
Go to sleep.

532
00:51:59,160 --> 00:52:00,702
You two stay with me!

533
00:56:31,546 --> 00:56:32,957
Dr. Hineman.

534
00:56:33,590 --> 00:56:36,793
You're trespassing.
I don't have visitors.

535
00:56:42,098 --> 00:56:45,099
That would be from the doll's eye,
the vine...

536
00:56:45,268 --> 00:56:48,601
...the baneberry that scratched you
during your illegal climb over my wall.

537
00:56:48,771 --> 00:56:52,603
It's not a true doll's eye.
It's a little hybrid I designed.

538
00:56:52,817 --> 00:56:56,565
Once the poison gets into your
bloodstream, you'll start to see...

539
00:56:56,779 --> 00:57:00,942
...the most extraordinary display
of blue objects.

540
00:57:01,117 --> 00:57:04,616
This just isn't your week, is it?

541
00:57:06,121 --> 00:57:07,616
Chief Anderton.

542
00:57:10,042 --> 00:57:11,619
I'm not a killer.

543
00:57:17,674 --> 00:57:19,133
You better drink this.

544
00:57:19,342 --> 00:57:23,387
Soon you won't be able to swallow,
and then you'll be totally buggered.

545
00:57:24,639 --> 00:57:25,884
All of it.

546
00:57:26,641 --> 00:57:30,057
Okay, now take a minute
to right yourself.

547
00:57:31,437 --> 00:57:35,020
Just what is it you think
I can do for you?

548
00:57:37,485 --> 00:57:41,897
You could tell me how someone
can fake a prevision.

549
00:57:42,114 --> 00:57:44,071
How would I know that?

550
00:57:44,450 --> 00:57:46,941
Because you invented Precrime.

551
00:57:48,996 --> 00:57:50,573
What's so funny?

552
00:57:51,081 --> 00:57:56,158
If the consequences of several genetic
mistakes and science gone haywire...

553
00:57:56,336 --> 00:57:59,207
...can be called an invention,
then I invented Precrime.

554
00:57:59,423 --> 00:58:01,415
- You don't seem proud.
- I'm not.

555
00:58:01,633 --> 00:58:04,800
I was trying to heal them,
not turn them into something else.

556
00:58:04,970 --> 00:58:07,757
- Heal who?
- The innocents we use to stop the guilty.

557
00:58:07,972 --> 00:58:11,176
You're talking about the Pre-Cogs.

558
00:58:11,392 --> 00:58:16,553
You think they came from a test tube?
They are merely the ones who survived.

559
00:58:16,773 --> 00:58:20,556
I was doing genetic research,
treating children of drug addicts.

560
00:58:20,776 --> 00:58:24,394
This was 10 years ago,
when neuroin first hit the streets.

561
00:58:24,613 --> 00:58:30,782
It was impure, not the engineered
cocktail popular among the educated.

562
00:58:31,704 --> 00:58:37,457
All of these kids were born with severe
brain damage. Most died before age 12.

563
00:58:37,668 --> 00:58:40,372
Those few who survived,
they had a gift.

564
00:58:40,545 --> 00:58:43,879
I call it a gift. For them,
it was more like a cosmic joke.

565
00:58:44,090 --> 00:58:46,842
They would wake up in the night,
curled in the corner...

566
00:58:47,052 --> 00:58:48,961
...screaming, clawing at the walls.

567
00:58:49,179 --> 00:58:53,508
Because when these children
closed their eyes at night...

568
00:58:53,683 --> 00:58:58,144
...they dreamt only of murder
over and over, one after the other.

569
00:58:58,312 --> 00:59:01,895
It didn't take for us long to realize
that the real nightmare was...

570
00:59:02,108 --> 00:59:07,066
...that these dreams were about to come
true, these murders were happening.

571
00:59:10,991 --> 00:59:13,399
You say some of the children died?

572
00:59:13,619 --> 00:59:16,822
So many of them.
Despite what we did for them.

573
00:59:17,039 --> 00:59:21,286
Or maybe because of what we
did to them. But it doesn't matter.

574
00:59:21,501 --> 00:59:24,288
It's a perfect system now, isn't it?

575
00:59:25,422 --> 00:59:27,545
I'm not going to commit murder.

576
00:59:27,757 --> 00:59:30,130
I've never met the man
I'm supposed to kill.

577
00:59:30,343 --> 00:59:34,590
And yet a chain of events has started
that will lead you to his murder.

578
00:59:34,806 --> 00:59:37,593
- Not if I stay away from him.
- Can you avoid a man you've never met?

579
00:59:37,809 --> 00:59:40,763
- You won't help?
- I can't help you. Nobody can.

580
00:59:40,978 --> 00:59:43,766
The Pre-Cogs are never wrong.

581
00:59:46,150 --> 00:59:48,273
But occasionally...

582
00:59:48,819 --> 00:59:50,942
...they do disagree.

583
00:59:52,448 --> 00:59:53,610
What?

584
00:59:53,908 --> 00:59:58,616
Most of the time, all three Pre-Cogs
will see an event in the same way...

585
00:59:58,787 --> 01:00:02,737
...but once in a while, one of them will
see things differently than the others.

586
01:00:02,916 --> 01:00:06,961
Jesus Christ.
Why didn't I know about this?

587
01:00:07,712 --> 01:00:10,916
Because these Minority Reports
are destroyed the instant they occur.

588
01:00:11,091 --> 01:00:12,253
Why?

589
01:00:12,425 --> 01:00:17,383
For Precrime to function, there can't
be any suggestion of fallibility.

590
01:00:17,555 --> 01:00:20,675
Who wants a justice system
that instills doubt?

591
01:00:20,850 --> 01:00:23,767
It may be reasonable,
but it's still doubt.

592
01:00:25,188 --> 01:00:28,023
Are you saying
I've haloed innocent people?

593
01:00:28,190 --> 01:00:31,939
I'm saying that every so often,
those accused of a Precrime...

594
01:00:32,111 --> 01:00:34,684
...just might have
an alternate future.

595
01:00:34,864 --> 01:00:38,778
Does Burgess know about this,
about this Minority Report?

596
01:00:38,993 --> 01:00:42,527
I used to joke with Lamar that
we were the parents of Precrime.

597
01:00:42,704 --> 01:00:47,615
Parents often see their children as they
want them to be and not as they are.

598
01:00:47,793 --> 01:00:52,953
Answer my question: Does Lamar
Burgess know about the Minority Report?

599
01:00:53,131 --> 01:00:54,791
Yes, of course, he knew.

600
01:00:54,966 --> 01:01:00,209
But at the time, we felt their existence
was an insignificant variable.

601
01:01:00,388 --> 01:01:02,345
Insignificant to you, maybe.

602
01:01:02,515 --> 01:01:06,299
But what about those people that
I put away with alternate futures?

603
01:01:06,519 --> 01:01:10,184
- My God, if the country knew...
- The system would collapse.

604
01:01:12,233 --> 01:01:14,854
- I believe in that system.
- Do you really?

605
01:01:15,027 --> 01:01:16,652
You wanna bring it down.

606
01:01:16,821 --> 01:01:20,735
You will bring it down
if you manage to kill your victim.

607
01:01:20,908 --> 01:01:25,985
That'll be the most spectacular public
display of how Precrime didn't work.

608
01:01:26,163 --> 01:01:29,117
- I'm not gonna kill anybody.
- Hold that thought.

609
01:01:29,291 --> 01:01:32,742
- Why should I trust you?
- You shouldn't trust anyone.

610
01:01:32,919 --> 01:01:36,169
Certainly not the attorney general,
who wants it all for himself.

611
01:01:36,339 --> 01:01:39,091
And not the young federal agent,
who wants your job.

612
01:01:39,300 --> 01:01:43,512
Not even the old man who just wants
to hang on to what he created.

613
01:01:43,680 --> 01:01:47,095
Don't trust anyone.
Just find the Minority Report.

614
01:01:49,018 --> 01:01:50,761
You said the Minority Report
is destroyed.

615
01:01:51,020 --> 01:01:54,721
The record is destroyed.
The original report still exists.

616
01:01:54,899 --> 01:02:00,141
I designed it so the report is stored
in a safe place, but not declared.

617
01:02:00,321 --> 01:02:02,609
What safe place is that?

618
01:02:02,781 --> 01:02:06,031
The safest place there is.

619
01:02:06,243 --> 01:02:09,197
Where is it?

620
01:02:11,331 --> 01:02:15,329
Inside the Pre-Cog who predicted it.

621
01:02:19,923 --> 01:02:24,466
All you have to do
is download it, darling.

622
01:02:26,054 --> 01:02:27,714
That's all, huh?

623
01:02:31,142 --> 01:02:33,977
Just walk into Precrime,
get into the temple...

624
01:02:34,145 --> 01:02:38,807
...somehow tap into these Pre-Cogs
and download this Minority Report.

625
01:02:38,983 --> 01:02:41,474
- If you have one.
- And then walk out.

626
01:02:41,652 --> 01:02:46,148
Actually, you'll have to run out.
But yes, that's what you have to do.

627
01:02:47,032 --> 01:02:49,072
You're insane.

628
01:02:49,701 --> 01:02:51,824
Or you think I am.

629
01:02:51,995 --> 01:02:57,202
I'll get eye-scanned a dozen times
before I get within 10 miles of Precrime.

630
01:02:57,375 --> 01:03:02,203
Sometimes in order to see the light,
you have to risk the dark.

631
01:03:02,380 --> 01:03:05,714
As a policeman...
Excuse me, as a former policeman...

632
01:03:05,884 --> 01:03:08,588
...I'm sure that you know
all sorts of people...

633
01:03:08,803 --> 01:03:12,089
...who can help you out
in this regard.

634
01:03:18,229 --> 01:03:21,265
It's funny how all
living organisms are alike.

635
01:03:21,440 --> 01:03:25,141
When the chips are down,
when the pressure is on...

636
01:03:25,319 --> 01:03:28,273
...every creature
on the face of the earth...

637
01:03:28,447 --> 01:03:31,898
...is interested in one thing
and one thing only:

638
01:03:32,910 --> 01:03:35,116
Its own survival.

639
01:03:36,747 --> 01:03:38,905
Find the Minority Report.

640
01:03:44,004 --> 01:03:46,755
How do I even know which one has it?

641
01:03:46,923 --> 01:03:50,257
It's always in the more gifted
of the three.

642
01:03:51,844 --> 01:03:53,754
Which one is that?

643
01:03:56,724 --> 01:03:58,598
The female.

644
01:04:01,687 --> 01:04:05,388
We've got three men in a room.
The victim is here...

645
01:04:05,566 --> 01:04:09,777
...John is here, and this
unidentified male, at the window.

646
01:04:09,945 --> 01:04:13,777
The adjacent building suggests
public housing, which means...

647
01:04:13,949 --> 01:04:16,784
- There's thousands like this one.
- They're everywhere.

648
01:04:16,952 --> 01:04:19,869
But he doesn't go there to kill Crow
for another 22 hours.

649
01:04:20,038 --> 01:04:22,245
This is Chief Anderton's space.

650
01:04:22,416 --> 01:04:24,325
- He's not here.
- He'll be back.

651
01:04:24,501 --> 01:04:28,249
I doubt that. I'm betting
he's somewhere in the Sprawl.

652
01:04:28,421 --> 01:04:32,253
He's smart enough to go
where billboards can't ID him.

653
01:04:32,425 --> 01:04:34,797
There's fewer consumers,
which means fewer scanners.

654
01:04:34,969 --> 01:04:39,216
- Why won't he just run?
- Because he thinks he's innocent.

655
01:04:40,475 --> 01:04:42,301
We concentrate on the Sprawl.

656
01:04:42,476 --> 01:04:45,513
We do fly-overs in ships,
with two spyder teams on the ground.

657
01:04:45,688 --> 01:04:50,017
Thermal scan the entire area. Read
anything with eyes and a heartbeat.

658
01:05:05,874 --> 01:05:07,154
Where is she?

659
01:05:25,685 --> 01:05:31,687
<i>Started blowing buttons for no reason
whatsoever, and I knew that.</i>

660
01:05:35,277 --> 01:05:37,353
This damn cold.

661
01:05:38,530 --> 01:05:42,777
Don't worry. I could cut open your
chest and sew a dead cat in there...

662
01:05:42,951 --> 01:05:47,613
...you wouldn't get an infection. Not
with the antibios I'll shoot into you.

663
01:05:47,789 --> 01:05:49,283
That's comforting.

664
01:05:49,457 --> 01:05:52,873
You do understand I can't just
give you new irises?

665
01:05:53,044 --> 01:05:54,503
Please, don't touch.

666
01:05:54,671 --> 01:05:58,620
Because the scanners would read the
new scar tissue, alarms will go off...

667
01:05:58,800 --> 01:06:01,373
...and large men with guns will appear.

668
01:06:03,846 --> 01:06:05,590
What was that?

669
01:06:05,765 --> 01:06:06,927
What was that?

670
01:06:07,099 --> 01:06:11,726
- It's anesthesia. It's all downhill...
- You always sneak up on your patients?

671
01:06:11,896 --> 01:06:16,024
You wouldn't break the hand
of a violinist before the concert.

672
01:06:16,192 --> 01:06:17,816
Please, relax.

673
01:06:22,364 --> 01:06:27,655
All I'm trying to tell you is that I'll
have to remove your eyes completely.

674
01:06:27,828 --> 01:06:28,990
I know.

675
01:06:29,913 --> 01:06:34,124
- I have to replace them with new ones.
- I know. But I wanna keep the old ones.

676
01:06:34,292 --> 01:06:37,957
- Why?
- Because my mother gave them to me.

677
01:06:38,129 --> 01:06:40,501
What's it to you?
You can't resell them.

678
01:06:40,673 --> 01:06:43,591
Whatever you say. It's your money.

679
01:06:50,850 --> 01:06:55,512
Let me introduce my gorgeous
assistant, Miss Van Eyck.

680
01:07:16,291 --> 01:07:20,703
- This is not a lot of money.
- It's all that I could safely move.

681
01:07:23,631 --> 01:07:25,256
Okay.

682
01:07:29,053 --> 01:07:32,422
- What did you give me?
- Smile medicine.

683
01:07:32,598 --> 01:07:35,089
Tell you what, since we go way back...

684
01:07:35,267 --> 01:07:39,561
...why don't I give you my old pal
discount? What do you say?

685
01:07:39,730 --> 01:07:41,972
You don't remember me, do you?

686
01:07:42,149 --> 01:07:45,648
- We know each other?
- Yes, we do.

687
01:07:45,903 --> 01:07:47,860
From where? D.C.?

688
01:07:48,030 --> 01:07:52,608
- Baltimore. The East Side.
- Baltimore? We go way back.

689
01:07:52,784 --> 01:07:56,829
Solomon P. Eddie, M.D.
I was a plastic surgeon.

690
01:07:56,997 --> 01:08:02,239
You remember? Specialized
in burn victims, mostly women.

691
01:08:02,419 --> 01:08:06,084
- I put you away.
- Yeah, you did.

692
01:08:07,882 --> 01:08:10,124
You made those tapes.

693
01:08:10,301 --> 01:08:12,874
They were performance pieces.

694
01:08:14,180 --> 01:08:18,343
- You set your patients on fire.
- I put them out.

