01:56:21,787 --> 01:56:24,622
They wanted me to think
Crow killed him.

1168
01:56:25,791 --> 01:56:27,333
But he didn't.

1169
01:56:28,919 --> 01:56:30,330
He didn't.

1170
01:56:32,089 --> 01:56:34,627
Why would they set you up?

1171
01:56:42,224 --> 01:56:45,141
Because I found out about her.

1172
01:56:46,061 --> 01:56:47,852
About who?

1173
01:56:48,063 --> 01:56:51,847
- How could I not have seen this?
- Seen what?

1174
01:56:53,068 --> 01:56:55,143
Anne Lively.

1175
01:56:57,655 --> 01:56:59,149
Agatha.

1176
01:57:03,870 --> 01:57:06,989
Dr. Hineman once said,
"The dead don't die...

1177
01:57:07,164 --> 01:57:09,240
...they look on and help. "

1178
01:57:10,000 --> 01:57:12,242
Remember that, John.

1179
01:57:13,337 --> 01:57:14,500
Agatha.

1180
01:57:14,672 --> 01:57:16,296
Sean.

1181
01:57:20,427 --> 01:57:22,883
He's on the beach now...

1182
01:57:23,513 --> 01:57:25,755
...toe in the water.

1183
01:57:26,850 --> 01:57:29,685
He's asking you to come in with him.

1184
01:57:30,353 --> 01:57:33,722
He's been racing his mother
up and down the sand.

1185
01:57:35,525 --> 01:57:38,395
There's so much love in this house.

1186
01:57:43,408 --> 01:57:45,317
He's 10 years old.

1187
01:57:47,745 --> 01:57:50,414
He's surrounded by animals.

1188
01:57:51,665 --> 01:57:53,954
He wants to be a vet.

1189
01:57:55,794 --> 01:58:00,540
You keep a rabbit for him,
a bird and a fox.

1190
01:58:02,050 --> 01:58:03,877
He's in high school.

1191
01:58:04,386 --> 01:58:07,221
He likes to run, like his father.

1192
01:58:07,723 --> 01:58:11,056
He runs the two-mile
and the long relay.

1193
01:58:12,394 --> 01:58:14,137
He's 23.

1194
01:58:15,563 --> 01:58:17,805
He's at a university.

1195
01:58:18,274 --> 01:58:21,477
He makes love
to a pretty girl named Claire.

1196
01:58:21,653 --> 01:58:24,108
He asks her to be his wife.

1197
01:58:24,739 --> 01:58:28,357
He calls here and tells Lara,
who cries.

1198
01:58:29,994 --> 01:58:31,987
He still runs...

1199
01:58:32,204 --> 01:58:36,451
...across the university and
in the stadium, where John watches.

1200
01:58:36,667 --> 01:58:41,210
Oh, God. He's running so fast,
just like his daddy.

1201
01:58:41,797 --> 01:58:46,008
He sees his daddy.
He wants to run to him.

1202
01:58:47,469 --> 01:58:52,047
But he's only 6 years old,
and he can't do it.

1203
01:58:52,557 --> 01:58:54,882
And the other man is so fast.

1204
01:58:58,730 --> 01:59:01,482
There was so much love in this house.

1205
01:59:02,734 --> 01:59:05,059
I want him back so bad.

1206
01:59:07,572 --> 01:59:09,363
So did she.

1207
01:59:10,074 --> 01:59:11,782
Can't you see?

1208
01:59:15,621 --> 01:59:18,824
She just wanted her little girl back.

1209
01:59:21,001 --> 01:59:23,243
But it was too late.

1210
01:59:24,922 --> 01:59:27,413
Her little girl was already gone.

1211
01:59:28,175 --> 01:59:29,752
She's still alive.

1212
01:59:31,386 --> 01:59:33,260
She didn't die.

1213
01:59:33,680 --> 01:59:35,589
But she's not alive.

1214
01:59:37,434 --> 01:59:38,928
Agatha?

1215
01:59:41,563 --> 01:59:42,938
Just tell me...

1216
01:59:43,523 --> 01:59:45,599
...who killed your mother?

1217
01:59:46,276 --> 01:59:48,398
Who killed Anne Lively?

1218
01:59:50,029 --> 01:59:54,940
I'm sorry, John,
but you're gonna have to run again.

1219
01:59:55,743 --> 01:59:57,901
- What?
- Run!

1220
02:00:14,761 --> 02:00:16,421
I love you.

1221
02:00:17,305 --> 02:00:20,092
- It's okay.
- You'll be fine with them.

1222
02:00:20,267 --> 02:00:23,054
- No! No!
- Stay with me. Stay with me.

1223
02:00:23,228 --> 02:00:25,683
- John, no.
- Don't talk.

1224
02:00:43,164 --> 02:00:44,492
John Anderton.

1225
02:00:45,791 --> 02:00:48,994
By mandate of the D.C.
Precrime Division...

1226
02:00:49,169 --> 02:00:54,330
...I'm placing you under arrest for the
murders of Leo Crow and Danny Witwer.

1227
02:00:57,511 --> 02:00:59,135
That's it.

1228
02:00:59,554 --> 02:01:01,298
That's my girl.

1229
02:01:03,141 --> 02:01:05,430
I was so worried about you.

1230
02:01:09,481 --> 02:01:11,272
Did he hurt you?

1231
02:01:14,319 --> 02:01:15,943
I missed you so much.

1232
02:01:16,112 --> 02:01:18,354
It's okay. Wally's here.

1233
02:01:19,073 --> 02:01:20,484
Wally's here.

1234
02:01:25,663 --> 02:01:29,079
You're a part of my flock now, John.

1235
02:01:29,291 --> 02:01:30,785
Welcome.

1236
02:01:31,752 --> 02:01:36,295
It's actually kind of a rush.
They say you have visions...

1237
02:01:36,465 --> 02:01:39,549
...that your life flashes
before your eyes...

1238
02:01:39,718 --> 02:01:43,169
...that all your dreams come true.

1239
02:01:59,946 --> 02:02:02,234
This is all my fault.

1240
02:02:03,241 --> 02:02:05,814
There was nothing anyone could do.

1241
02:02:10,247 --> 02:02:13,034
I thought you might want
to have those.

1242
02:02:18,839 --> 02:02:23,916
I haven't worn this in years. I wanted
to make sure it fits before tonight.

1243
02:02:24,094 --> 02:02:25,422
You look great.

1244
02:02:25,595 --> 02:02:29,842
I knew he was having trouble
for some time, yet I did nothing.

1245
02:02:30,016 --> 02:02:33,551
<i>- The guy from USA Today is here.
- Tell him not now.</i>

1246
02:02:33,728 --> 02:02:37,179
- He just wanted a few minutes before...
- Not now!

1247
02:02:39,734 --> 02:02:43,269
- I thought you were retiring.
- Well, I was.

1248
02:02:43,488 --> 02:02:49,241
But this incident with John made me
realize the fragility of all this.

1249
02:02:49,785 --> 02:02:53,119
This is John's legacy
as much as it is my own.

1250
02:02:53,914 --> 02:02:57,365
Now I have an obligation
to protect that.

1251
02:02:57,918 --> 02:03:01,453
Lara, I know how difficult
this is for you.

1252
02:03:01,630 --> 02:03:04,999
But maybe you can find
some closure in the fact...

1253
02:03:05,175 --> 02:03:09,636
...that John finally found
the man who killed your son.

1254
02:03:12,474 --> 02:03:13,802
Who's Anne Lively?

1255
02:03:16,644 --> 02:03:19,100
- Who?
- Anne Lively.

1256
02:03:19,564 --> 02:03:23,478
John was talking about her
right before they took him.

1257
02:03:23,651 --> 02:03:25,809
I don't know who that is.

1258
02:03:26,988 --> 02:03:32,195
John said something about him being
set up because he found out about her.

1259
02:03:32,368 --> 02:03:37,326
- Well, we know why John was tagged.
- He also said Crow was a fake.

1260
02:03:37,498 --> 02:03:42,041
And Witwer? He was killed with
John's gun inside John's apartment.

1261
02:03:42,211 --> 02:03:46,422
Do you know the reason why
John came here to work for you?

1262
02:03:46,590 --> 02:03:47,965
- Sean.
- Yes.

1263
02:03:48,759 --> 02:03:52,044
He came here to work for you
because he thought...

1264
02:03:52,220 --> 02:03:56,847
...if he could just stop
that kind of thing from happening...

1265
02:03:57,517 --> 02:04:00,720
- I understand.
- No, I don't think you do.

1266
02:04:00,895 --> 02:04:05,640
Sir, they wanna start
the press conference in two minutes.

1267
02:04:05,817 --> 02:04:06,979
Lara...

1268
02:04:07,443 --> 02:04:10,314
...John was the best cop I ever knew...

1269
02:04:10,529 --> 02:04:13,364
...and, in some ways,
also the best man.

1270
02:04:13,532 --> 02:04:15,988
But the scars he carried around...

1271
02:04:16,160 --> 02:04:21,534
Well, I know he'd want us to honor
the good things we remember about him.

1272
02:04:21,707 --> 02:04:27,377
And I also know why he married you:
You're as stubborn as he is.

1273
02:04:27,546 --> 02:04:31,923
- Lamar...
- Do you know how to tie one of these?

1274
02:04:32,092 --> 02:04:36,504
Could you please give me a hand?
I'm all thumbs, as you see.

1275
02:04:44,354 --> 02:04:47,141
Listen, I'll tell you what I'll do.

1276
02:04:47,315 --> 02:04:51,609
First thing Monday,
I'll look over the Witwer evidence.

1277
02:04:51,777 --> 02:04:55,442
And I'll have Gideon
run the Containment files...

1278
02:04:55,614 --> 02:04:58,651
...see if anyone drowned a woman
by the name of...

1279
02:04:58,826 --> 02:05:01,613
What did you say her name was?

1280
02:05:03,706 --> 02:05:05,413
Anne Lively.

1281
02:05:06,041 --> 02:05:08,579
But I never said she drowned.

1282
02:05:28,438 --> 02:05:33,265
- Sir, the press conference is starting.
- I'll be right there.

1283
02:05:37,947 --> 02:05:40,354
We'll talk about this later.

1284
02:05:41,116 --> 02:05:45,695
Perhaps tomorrow,
I'll come by the cottage.

1285
02:06:22,448 --> 02:06:24,986
I'd like a word with my husband.

1286
02:06:25,701 --> 02:06:28,737
You're not authorized.

1287
02:06:28,954 --> 02:06:31,659
How did you get in here?

1288
02:06:40,340 --> 02:06:41,668
Thank you.

1289
02:06:41,842 --> 02:06:47,180
Ladies and gentlemen, Lamar Burgess,
director of the new National Precrime.

1290
02:06:49,807 --> 02:06:53,675
On behalf of your staff,
we present you with this.

1291
02:06:53,853 --> 02:06:57,685
- Congratulations, sir.
- My God.

1292
02:06:58,816 --> 02:07:00,310
How did you get this?

1293
02:07:00,484 --> 02:07:03,604
I padded your expense account
for six months.

1294
02:07:06,031 --> 02:07:09,863
Revolvers like this one
were given to generals...

1295
02:07:10,035 --> 02:07:13,202
...at the end of the Civil War
by their troops.

1296
02:07:13,372 --> 02:07:17,321
The cylinders were loaded
with five gold-plated bullets...

1297
02:07:17,501 --> 02:07:20,786
...to symbolize the end
of the destruction and death...

1298
02:07:20,962 --> 02:07:23,453
...that had ripped the country apart
for five years.

1299
02:07:23,632 --> 02:07:27,131
Ladies and gentlemen,
with Precrime going national...

1300
02:07:27,302 --> 02:07:31,346
...maybe we can all look forward
to a time when none of us...

1301
02:07:31,514 --> 02:07:34,848
...will have to discharge
another firearm ever again.

1302
02:07:36,185 --> 02:07:40,894
Now enjoy yourselves.
Enjoy yourselves! That's an order.

1303
02:07:43,776 --> 02:07:48,070
Does this mean we can finally use
the lake house on weekends?

1304
02:07:50,824 --> 02:07:52,069
Hello.

1305
02:07:52,242 --> 02:07:54,733
Yes. Right away.

1306
02:07:55,037 --> 02:07:58,156
- Excuse me, so sorry.
- Excuse me.

1307
02:07:58,373 --> 02:07:59,749
- Sir?
- Yes.

1308
02:07:59,917 --> 02:08:03,617
Sir, you have an emergency call
on your private line.

1309
02:08:04,713 --> 02:08:06,421
Yes, this is Burgess.

1310
02:08:06,590 --> 02:08:11,168
<i>Hello, Lamar. I just wanted
to congratulate you. You did it.</i>

1311
02:08:11,344 --> 02:08:13,835
<i>You created a world without murder.</i>

1312
02:08:14,013 --> 02:08:17,180
Everyone wants your name on a hat.
Can you sign these?

1313
02:08:17,350 --> 02:08:19,805
<i>All you had to do was kill someone
to do it.</i>

1314
02:08:24,565 --> 02:08:25,596
A-room. Jad.

1315
02:08:26,609 --> 02:08:29,942
Jad, it's Lara. John needs a favor.

1316
02:08:30,154 --> 02:08:34,732
<i>- What are you talking about?
- Agatha's mother, Anne Lively.</i>

1317
02:08:34,908 --> 02:08:39,238
<i>Just a junkie who had a kid once
and had to give her up, but surprise!</i>

1318
02:08:39,413 --> 02:08:42,367
<i>She cleaned herself up,
and she wanted her daughter back.</i>

1319
02:08:42,541 --> 02:08:44,498
<i>She wanted Agatha.</i>

1320
02:08:47,003 --> 02:08:51,416
Jad, you getting this? It's from the
female only. No time or incident data.

1321
02:08:51,591 --> 02:08:54,047
It isn't the future.
It already happened.

1322
02:08:54,219 --> 02:08:57,967
<i>And the problem was, without Agatha,
there was no Precrime.</i>

1323
02:08:58,139 --> 02:09:02,931
<i>She's the strongest of the three.
Without Agatha, you had nothing.</i>

1324
02:09:03,102 --> 02:09:08,523
<i>You wouldn't be where you are now,
standing there, signing autographs.</i>

1325
02:09:16,365 --> 02:09:19,781
- What are you doing?
- What are you doing with that?

1326
02:09:19,952 --> 02:09:23,534
- What you up to, big man?
- Think before you send that.

1327
02:09:23,705 --> 02:09:24,737
Slow down.

1328
02:09:45,351 --> 02:09:50,060
<i>Now you had to get rid of Anne Lively,
which presented a problem:</i>

1329
02:09:50,231 --> 02:09:53,896
<i>How can you kill her
without the Pre-Cogs seeing it?</i>

1330
02:09:54,068 --> 02:09:58,315
<i>Simple. Use a system
you control against her.</i>

1331
02:09:58,530 --> 02:10:03,738
<i>You hired someone to kill her, knowing
the Pre-Cogs would see that murder.</i>

1332
02:10:03,911 --> 02:10:07,445
<i>You lured Anne Lively
out to the lake...</i>

1333
02:10:07,623 --> 02:10:11,620
<i>... with the promise of reuniting her
with her daughter.</i>

1334
02:10:56,127 --> 02:10:58,120
<i>Where's my daughter?</i>

1335
02:11:05,386 --> 02:11:06,584
<i>Where?</i>

1336
02:11:08,639 --> 02:11:09,920
Run!

1337
02:11:13,352 --> 02:11:14,467
Run!

1338
02:11:26,115 --> 02:11:29,448
<i>When you were all alone,
you killed her yourself...</i>

1339
02:11:29,618 --> 02:11:33,568
<i>... in the same way the Pre-Cogs
predicted your John Doe would kill her.</i>

1340
02:11:33,747 --> 02:11:36,664
<i>You made the real murder
look like an echo...</i>

1341
02:11:36,833 --> 02:11:41,578
<i>... knowing the tech would do what
he was trained to do: Disregard it.</i>

1342
02:11:47,343 --> 02:11:51,804
<i>Anne Lively became
just another missing person.</i>

1343
02:11:52,432 --> 02:11:55,598
<i>So, what are you gonna do, Lamar?</i>

1344
02:11:56,352 --> 02:11:58,261
<i>What are you gonna do?</i>

1345
02:12:09,406 --> 02:12:10,735
We got a Red Ball!

1346
02:12:16,913 --> 02:12:19,831
Think about the lives
that little girl has saved.

1347
02:12:20,000 --> 02:12:22,870
Think about the lives
that little girl has saved.

1348
02:12:23,044 --> 02:12:27,623
Think of all the lives she will save.
She could have saved Sean.

1349
02:12:27,799 --> 02:12:30,372
Don't you ever say his name!

1350
02:12:32,595 --> 02:12:35,762
You used the memory of my dead son
to set me up.

1351
02:12:35,932 --> 02:12:38,932
You used the memory of my dead son
to set me up.

1352
02:12:39,101 --> 02:12:42,102
You knew that would
drive me to murder.

1353
02:12:42,271 --> 02:12:45,687
- What are you gonna do now, Lamar?
- What are you gonna do now, Lamar?

1354
02:12:45,858 --> 02:12:47,850
- How are you gonna...?
- Shut me up?

1355
02:12:48,027 --> 02:12:50,352
Forgive me, John.

1356
02:12:58,704 --> 02:13:00,495
<i>Forgive me, John.</i>

1357
02:13:12,091 --> 02:13:13,420
Lamar.

1358
02:13:13,843 --> 02:13:15,254
It's over.

1359
02:13:15,928 --> 02:13:21,219
The question you have to ask is,
what are you gonna do now?

1360
02:13:34,405 --> 02:13:37,441
No doubt the Pre-Cogs have
already seen this.

1361
02:13:37,616 --> 02:13:39,276
No doubt.

1362
02:13:40,285 --> 02:13:42,610
You see the dilemma, don't you?

1363
02:13:43,288 --> 02:13:47,701
If you don't kill me, Pre-Cogs were
wrong and Precrime is over.

1364
02:13:48,752 --> 02:13:52,286
If you do kill me, you go away...

1365
02:13:52,797 --> 02:13:57,258
...but it proves the system works.
Pre-Cogs were right.

1366
02:14:03,349 --> 02:14:06,718
So, what are you gonna do now?

1367
02:14:08,020 --> 02:14:10,013
What's it worth?

1368
02:14:10,815 --> 02:14:13,140
Just one more murder.

1369
02:14:15,986 --> 02:14:21,111
You'll rot in hell with a halo, but
people will still believe in Precrime.

1370
02:14:21,283 --> 02:14:25,327
All you have to do is kill me,
like they said you would.

1371
02:14:28,665 --> 02:14:30,243
Except...

1372
02:14:31,126 --> 02:14:33,581
...you know your own future...

1373
02:14:33,795 --> 02:14:37,413
...which means you can change it
if you want to.

1374
02:14:38,466 --> 02:14:41,502
You still have a choice, Lamar.

1375
02:14:41,969 --> 02:14:43,843
Like I did.

1376
02:14:48,517 --> 02:14:51,269
Yes, I have a choice...

1377
02:14:52,563 --> 02:14:54,556
...and I made it.

1378
02:14:55,482 --> 02:14:57,475
Forgive me, John.

1379
02:14:59,069 --> 02:15:00,861
Forgive me.

1380
02:15:06,118 --> 02:15:07,826
Forgive me, my boy.

1381
02:15:26,471 --> 02:15:28,048
Lamar!

1382
02:15:39,233 --> 02:15:44,060
<i>In 2054, the six-year Precrime
experiment was abandoned.</i>

1383
02:15:51,495 --> 02:15:54,994
<i>All prisoners were unconditionally
pardoned and released...</i>

1384
02:15:55,165 --> 02:15:59,458
<i>... although police departments
kept watch on many of them for years.</i>

1385
02:16:47,215 --> 02:16:49,587
<i>Agatha and the twins...</i>

1386
02:16:49,759 --> 02:16:53,128
<i>... were transferred
to an undisclosed location...</i>

1387
02:16:53,971 --> 02:16:57,554
<i>... a place where they could
find relief from their gifts...</i>

1388
02:16:57,850 --> 02:17:01,848
<i>... a place where they could
live out their lives in peace.</i>

